PN,31102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1776898985
OL,3,CGibraltar's monkey's eat mud 'to
OL,4,Csoothe upset stomachs from tourist
OL,5,Cjunk food'
OL,7,FScientists observing the monkeys found
OL,8,Fthat geophagy ` the deliberate
OL,9,Fconsumption of soil ` was highest when
OL,10,Fthe macaques ate high levels of food
OL,11,Ffrom tourists.
OL,13,FThey think the behaviour is likely to
OL,14,Fhave been learned socially, as
OL,15,Fdifferent troops of monkeys have
OL,16,Fpreferences for certain types of soil.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
