OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1776898985
OL,3,CGibraltar's monkey's eat mud 'to
OL,4,Csoothe upset stomachs from tourist
OL,5,Cjunk food'
OL,7,F"We think they are eating the soil to
OL,8,Fprotect themselves against the adverse
OL,9,Feffects junk food can trigger," said
OL,10,FDr Sylvain Lemoine, Assistant
OL,11,FProfessor in Biological Anthropology
OL,12,Fat the University of Cambridge.
OL,14,FSoil ingestion can help to rebalance
OL,15,Fthe gut and relieve symptoms from
OL,16,Fupset stomachs, he explained.
OL,18,FScientists believe the dirt also
OL,19,Fprovides bacteria and minerals absent
OL,20,Ffrom junk food.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1776898985
OL,3,CGibraltar's monkey's eat mud 'to
OL,4,Csoothe upset stomachs from tourist
OL,5,Cjunk food'
OL,7,FIn a study published in Scientific
OL,8,FReports, the scientists found that the
OL,9,Fmonkeys ate mud more in areas where
OL,10,Fthere were more tourists and that
OL,11,Fgeophagy was more common in the
OL,12,Fsummer, when tourist numbers peaked.
OL,14,FGeophagy is common in monkeys, apes,
OL,15,Flemurs and other non-human primates,
OL,16,Fbut why it happens is still being
OL,17,Fdebated. The scientists suspect that
OL,18,Fthe Gibralta macaques ate soil to
OL,19,Fprotect their stomachs from hard to
OL,20,Fdigest human food.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
