FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1776898985
OL,3,CGibraltar's monkey's eat mud 'to
OL,4,Csoothe upset stomachs from tourist
OL,5,Cjunk food'
OL,7,FGibraltarian authorities are
OL,8,Fresponsible for feeding the macaques a
OL,9,Fdiet of fruit, vegetables and seeds.
OL,10,FThe foods they might pick up from
OL,11,Ftourists, such as ice cream or crisps,
OL,12,Fare often high in calories, sugar,
OL,13,Fsalt, fat and dairy and low in fibre.
OL,15,FLemoine told ITV News that tourists
OL,16,Fshould follow the rules and not feed
OL,17,Fthe monkeys. He added they should also
OL,18,Fbe careful with carrying food in the
OL,19,Fbottom of prams or when taking snacks
OL,20,Fout of their pockets, as the monkeys
OL,21,Fmight snatch them.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
